<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2023-03-18T11:58:26.230Z" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Degrees-of-Freedom</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>Degrees-of-Freedom</keyword><keyword>DOF</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Degrees-of-Freedom</text> (DOF) of a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Kinematic-Chain">kinematic-chain</link> has a number of definitions. One definition is: The number of independent coordinates that are needed to define the position of an Part or a kinematic-chain.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Use the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Gruebler Equation</text> to calculate the Degrees-of-Freedom of each kinematic-chain. For planar kinematic-chains, it is: <equation style="vertical-align:text-bottom" font-size="22"><![CDATA[F = 3.\left( n-1 \right)-2.l]]></equation></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">F - degrees-of-freedom, n - number of Parts, l - number of joints</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">An important related term is <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Mobility">Mobility</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
